  Critical Bugs Found & Fixed

  1. Prisma transaction timeout (was crashing on first run — 3 resumes failed)
  - Root cause: 5s default timeout, some profile saves with 14+ achievements took 5.1–5.2s   
  - Fixed: prisma.$transaction(..., { timeout: 30000 })

  2. Scanned/image PDF returns near-zero text
  - Kurian_John_Resume_UC.pdf extracted only 16 characters (image-based PDF)
  - System silently continued, generated cover letters using the previous profile's data from   the DB — a serious data integrity bug (wrong person's letter)
  - Fixed: Extract route now returns HTTP 400 with a clear scanned-PDF message if text < 100 
  chars

  3. JSON parser failing on large resumes (MI-Resume, Vijay CV)
  - Two resumes (3.9K and 8.0K chars) caused Llama to return JSON wrapped in prose that the  
  parser couldn't handle
  - Fixed: parseLLMJson now tries four strategies: direct parse → {...} block → strip JS     
  comments then retry → [...] array block

  4. Frontend swallowed server error messages
  - Showed generic "Failed to extract resume. Please check your content" instead of the      
  specific error
  - Fixed: Now surfaces the actual server message (including the scanned PDF guidance)       

